            "content": "; Regression test for issue #742: ledger stats ignores -p until (BZ#742)\n; https://github.com/ledger/ledger/issues/742\n;\n; The stats command must respect the period specification (`-p \"until DATE\"`),\n; --end, --begin, and --limit filters.  Prior to the fix, the stats command\n; walked the entire journal unconditionally via family_details(), so those\n; filters were silently ignored.  With the command now participating in the\n; post filter chain, its output reflects the restricted range.\n\n2012-02-28 * Test\n    E               30.00 EUR\n    F\n\n2012-02-29 * Test\n    E               30.00 EUR\n    F\n\n2012-03-24 * Test\n    A               30.00 EUR\n    B\n\n; -p \"until DATE\" expands to \"date < DATE\", so \"until 2012-03-01\" includes\n; Feb 28 and Feb 29 only.  The statistics must reflect just those two\n; transactions: 2 accounts (E, F) rather than all 4, and 4 postings rather\n; than 6.  `--now` pins CURRENT_DATE() so the recency counters are stable.\ntest stats -p \"until 2012-03-01\" --now \"2012-03-31\"\nTime period: 12-Feb-28 to 12-Feb-29 (2 days)\n\n  Files these postings came from:\n    $FILE\n\n  Unique payees:               1\n  Unique accounts:             2\n\n  Number of postings:          4 (2 per day)\n  Uncleared postings:          0\n\n  Days since last post:       31\n  Posts in last 7 days:        0\n  Posts in last 30 days:       0\n  Posts seen this month:       0\nend test\n\n; --end 2012/03/01 is equivalent to -p \"until 2012-03-01\" for stats purposes.\ntest stats --end 2012/03/01 --now \"2012-03-31\"\nTime period: 12-Feb-28 to 12-Feb-29 (2 days)\n\n  Files these postings came from:\n    $FILE\n\n  Unique payees:               1\n  Unique accounts:             2\n\n  Number of postings:          4 (2 per day)\n  Uncleared postings:          0\n\n  Days since last post:       31\n  Posts in last 7 days:        0\n  Posts in last 30 days:       0\n  Posts seen this month:       0\nend test\n\n; --begin excludes postings before the date.  \"--begin 2012/03/01\" excludes\n; Feb 28 and Feb 29, leaving just the 2012-03-24 transaction.\ntest stats --begin 2012/03/01 --now \"2012-03-31\"\nTime period: 12-Mar-24 to 12-Mar-24 (1 days)\n\n  Files these postings came from:\n    $FILE\n\n  Unique payees:               1\n  Unique accounts:             2\n\n  Number of postings:          2 (2 per day)\n  Uncleared postings:          0\n\n  Days since last post:        7\n  Posts in last 7 days:        2\n  Posts in last 30 days:       2\n  Posts seen this month:       2\nend test\n\n; Account queries reach stats through the --limit predicate, so filtering\n; by account name must also narrow the reported statistics.\ntest stats ^A --now \"2012-03-31\"\nTime period: 12-Mar-24 to 12-Mar-24 (1 days)\n\n  Files these postings came from:\n    $FILE\n\n  Unique payees:               1\n  Unique accounts:             1\n\n  Number of postings:          1 (1 per day)\n  Uncleared postings:          0\n\n  Days since last post:        7\n  Posts in last 7 days:        1\n  Posts in last 30 days:       1\n  Posts seen this month:       1\nend test\n",
